Pills Component — `$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills`

Horizontal selection pills with optional filtering and external sync.

Parameters:

|!Parameter |!Default |!Description |
|`elements` |`""` |Space-separated list of element values to display |
|`selection` |`"multi"` |`"multi"` (toggle) or `"single"` (replace) |
|`filterable` |`"no"` |`"no"`, `"yes"` (popup search), or `"inline"` (search input above pills) |
|`sync-tiddler` |`""` |External tiddler to sync selection to (auto-generated if blank) |
|`sync-field` |`"text"` |Field on sync-tiddler to store selection |
|`state` |auto |State tiddler prefix (auto-qualified if blank) |
|`instid` |auto |Unique instance ID (auto-qualified if blank) |

Slots:

|!Slot |!Variables |!Description |
|`view` |`element` |Custom rendering of each pill. Default: plain text of element value |
|`on-select` |`element`, `modifier` |Action widgets fired after selection changes |

Selection behavior:

- **multi**: Clicking toggles element in a space-separated list. Multiple elements can be active.
- **single**: Clicking replaces the current value. Only one element active at a time.
- Selected pills get CSS class `.selected`.

Reading the selection externally:

The selection is stored in `sync-tiddler` / `sync-field`. If you did not provide `sync-tiddler`, the selection is in the auto-generated state tiddler. To read it reliably, always set an explicit `sync-tiddler`.

```
<!-- Store selection in MyTiddler/tags field -->
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
  elements="Tag1 Tag2 Tag3"
  selection="multi"
  sync-tiddler="MyTiddler"
  sync-field="tags"/>

<!-- Read it elsewhere -->
{{MyTiddler!!tags}}
```

Filtering modes:

- `filterable="no"` — all pills always visible
- `filterable="yes"` — click the arrow icon to open a popup search input; pills not matching the search text are hidden
- `filterable="inline"` — search input rendered above the pills; pills not matching are hidden

Navigate deeper: llm_help("components/facades/pills/create") for step-by-step creation guide
